10/11/2003
BELGRADE, Serbia-Montenegro -- Serbia's ruling coalition, the Democratic Opposition of Serbia, will meet on Wednesday (12 November) to consider the possibility of scheduling early general elections, according to Deputy Serbian Prime Minister Nebojsa Covic. He added Sunday that the agenda would include a look at preparations for the 16 November presidential elections.
In other news, former Yugoslav Army Chief of Staff General Nebojsa Pavkovic said Saturday that he has no plans to surrender to the UN war crimes tribunal despite his recent indictment. (Beta, B92 - 10/11/03; BBC, Beta, B92, Serbian Radio - 09/11/03)
